{"type":"message","id":"c2120adc","parentId":"ea073dab","timestamp":"2026-03-03T10:01:00.539Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I found the Finnhub Market News endpoint. However, it doesn't have a \"heat\" score filter. The user asked for热度≥80, which seems to refer to a sentiment/interest score.\n\nLooking at the Alpha Vantage news sentiment API - it has sentiment scores. Let me check if Finnhub has a similar feature or if I should use Alpha Vantage instead.\n\nActually, looking at the user's request again: they specifically asked for Finnhub. Let me first try to get the Finnhub market news and see what data it returns. Maybe the news items have some kind of heat/interest metric.\n\nLet me execute the Finnhub market news with category=general to see what data comes back.","thinkingSignature":"930e861f96a3a0d7c09f5bc70ec92abb6ab727cd805832581ef8e1196f319cd6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_d4jbekycfqv6_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace && node scripts/qveris_tool.mjs execute finnhub.market.news.list.v1 --search-id 7ed049a6-e8c5-466a-80cd-fdf79f50e959 --params '{\"category\": \"general\"}'","timeout":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":13433,"output":234,"cacheRead":13984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27651,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772532028550}}
