{"type":"message","id":"976ff75c","parentId":"6bb8145c","timestamp":"2026-03-03T10:03:56.541Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The API is returning the same error. This suggests that either:1. The tool definition on QVeris side is wrong2. The tool expects parameters in a different format (maybe as query parameters instead of body?)Let me try a different approach - maybe I should look for other financial news APIs that actually work. Let me search for financial news APIs that work reliably.Actually wait - looking at the error, it says \"缺少必需的查询参数\" which means \"missing required query parameter\". This could mean the API is expecting the parameter as a query string parameter, not in the body. Let me see if there's another working news API. The Alpha Vantage news might work differently.\n\nLet me try Alpha Vantage:","thinkingSignature":"a58b9f43fc7fb9a45a6acca9f23d16b64bcc95506ce6e85a42d0d35610f62ef5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lc48r2ojyfa8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -X POST https://qveris.ai/api/v1/tools/execute \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $QVERIS_API_KEY\" \\\n  -d '{\"tool_id\": \"alphavantage.news_sentiment.query.v1.7aca3c4a\", \"params\": {\"function\": \"NEWS_SENTIMENT\"}}' | head -c 3000","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":25472,"output":270,"cacheRead":13984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":39726,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772532227659}}
