{"type":"message","id":"9b48623b","parentId":"08735aaf","timestamp":"2026-03-03T10:04:08.314Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_un2n0j24hzhh_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"weather API\",\n  \"total\": 10,\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"visualcrossing.timeline.retrieve.v1\",\n      \"name\": \"Weather Timeline\",\n      \"description\": \"Retrieve weather timeline data for a specified location.\",\n      \"params\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"location\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Location identifier, such as a city name or coordinates.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"unitGroup\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Unit group for measurements.\"\n          },\n          \"enum\": [\n            \"us\",\n            \"metric\"\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"contentType\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Response content type.\"\n          },\n          \"enum\": [\n            \"json\",\n            \"csv\",\n            \"xml\"\n          ]\n        }\n      ],\n      \"examples\": {\n        \"sample_parameters\": {\n          \"location\": \"New York\"\n        }\n      },\n      \"provider_description\": \"API provider for Visual Crossing Weather API\",\n      \"stats\": {\n        \"avg_execution_time_ms\": 0.363,\n        \"success_rate\": 1\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"visualcrossing.timeline.list.v1\",\n      \"name\": \"Get Weather Timeline\",\n      \"description\": \"Retrieve weather data timeline for a specified location and date range\",\n      \"params\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"location\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Location such as city and state\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"startDate\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Start date in YYYY-MM-DD format\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"endDate\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"End date in YYYY-MM-DD format\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"examples\": {\n        \"sample_parameters\": {\n          \"endDate\": \"2023-10-07\",\n          \"location\": \"New York,US\",\n          \"startDate\": \"2023-10-01\"\n        }\n      },\n      \"provider_description\": \"API provider for Visual Crossing Weather API\",\n      \"stats\": {\n        \"avg_execution_time_ms\": 0.6,\n        \"success_rate\": 1\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"weather_gov.icons.retrieve.v1.81912464\",\n      \"name\": \"icons_summary\",\n      \"description\": \"Returns a list of icon codes and textual descriptions. Icon services in API are deprecated.\",\n      \"provider_description\": \"The National Weather Service (NWS) API allows developers access to critical forecasts, alerts, and observations, along with other weather data. The API is based upon JSON-LD to promote machine data discovery.\",\n      \"stats\": {\n        \"avg_execution_time_ms\": 0.594,\n        \"success_rate\": 1\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"here_technologies.destination_weather.version.retrieve.v3.72b1486a\",\n      \"name\": \"Retrieve Service Version\",\n      \"description\": \"Returns the version of the Destination Weather API service.\",\n      \"provider_description\": \"API for processing large numbers of Geocode, Reverse Geocoding, and Lookup by ID requests.\\n## \\\"ALPHA\\\" & \\\"BETA\\\" tags\\n\\nAPI requests parameters and response fields can be tagged with one of the following maturity qualifiers: alpha, beta\\n- \\\"ALPHA\\\" tagged features are in mid-stage development. They can change or in rare cases be removed. No backward compatibility is guaranteed nor bug service level agreement (SLA) do apply. Customers using ALPHA features are advised not use them in production.\\n- \\\"BETA\\\" tagged features are in end-stage development. They are backward compatible and can not be removed. They have no major bug, but coverage, quality, performance, or test coverage is not considered final. Customers can safely use BETA features in their applications if they accept those limitations and potential behavior refinements.\\n\\n## \\\"RESTRICTED\\\" tag\\n\\nAPI requests parameters and response fields can be tagged with the privilege qualifier \\\"RESTRICTED\\\". Such features are only available to customers having a specific contract with HERE. Unauthorized usages are typically leading to a http status code 403.\",\n      \"stats\": {\n        \"avg_execution_time_ms\": 0,\n        \"success_rate\": 0\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"here_technologies.destination_weather.report.retrieve.v3.6b34d07e\",\n      \"name\": \"Retrieve Weather Report\",\n      \"description\": \"Get a weather report containing observations, forecasts, alerts, or astronomy data based on the specified products parameter.\",\n      \"params\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"products\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Comma-separated list of product types to include in the response.\"\n          },\n          \"enum\": [\n            \"observation\",\n            \"forecast7days\",\n            \"forecast7daysSimple\",\n            \"forecastHourly\",\n            \"alerts\",\n            \"nwsAlerts\",\n            \"forecastAstronomy\"\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"location\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Geographic location (e.g., latitude,longitude or place name) for which to retrieve the weather report.\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"examples\": {\n        \"sample_parameters\": {\n          \"location\": \"52.5168,13.3889\",\n          \"products\": \"observation,forecast7days\"\n        }\n      },\n      \"provider_description\": \"API for processing large numbers of Geocode, Reverse Geocoding, and Lookup by ID requests.\\n## \\\"ALPHA\\\" & \\\"BETA\\\" tags\\n\\nAPI requests parameters and response fields can be tagged with one of the following maturity qualifiers: alpha, beta\\n- \\\"ALPHA\\\" tagged features are in mid-stage development. They can change or in rare cases be removed. No backward compatibility is guaranteed nor bug service level agreement (SLA) do apply. Customers using ALPHA features are advised not use them in production.\\n- \\\"BETA\\\" tagged features are in end-stage development. They are backward compatible and can not be removed. They have no major bug, but coverage, quality, performance, or test coverage is not considered final. Customers can safely use BETA features in their applications if they accept those limitations and potential behavior refinements.\\n\\n## \\\"RESTRICTED\\\" tag\\n\\nAPI requests parameters and response fields can be tagged with the privilege qualifier \\\"RESTRICTED\\\". Such features are only available to customers having a specific contract with HERE. Unauthorized usages are typically leading to a http status code 403.\",\n      \"stats\": {\n        \"avg_execution_time_ms\": 0,\n        \"success_rate\": 0\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"here_technologies.destination_weather.report.retrieve.v3.bc6bde88\",\n      \"name\": \"Retrieve Weather Report\",\n      \"description\": \"Get a weather report containing observations, forecasts, alerts, or astronomy data based on the specified products parameter.\",\n      \"params\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"products\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Comma-separated list of product types to include in the response.\"\n          },\n          \"enum\": [\n            \"observation\",\n            \"forecast7days\",\n            \"forecast7daysSimple\",\n            \"forecastHourly\",\n            \"alerts\",\n            \"nwsAlerts\",\n            \"forecastAstronomy\"\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"geocode\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Latitude and longitude coordinates (e.g., 'lat,lon') to specify the location for the weather report.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"locationId\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Unique identifier for a known location (alternative to geocode).\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"examples\": {\n        \"sample_parameters\": {\n          \"geocode\": \"40.7128,-74.0060\",\n          \"products\": \"observation\"\n        }\n      },\n      \"provider_description\": \"API for processing large numbers of Geocode, Reverse Geocoding, and Lookup by ID requests.\\n## \\\"ALPHA\\\" & \\\"BETA\\\" tags\\n\\nAPI requests parameters and response fields can be tagged with one of the following maturity qualifiers: alpha, beta\\n- \\\"ALPHA\\\" tagged features are in mid-stage development. They can change or in rare cases be removed. No backward compatibility is guaranteed nor bug service level agreement (SLA) do apply. Customers using ALPHA features are advised not use them in production.\\n- \\\"BETA\\\" tagged features are in end-stage development. They are backward compatible and can not be removed. They have no major bug, but coverage, qu