{"type":"message","id":"76f7707f","parentId":"842a4e38","timestamp":"2026-03-03T10:04:30.933Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so the tool execution works when there are no required parameters. The issue seems to be specifically with passing parameters. Let me see what the API documentation says about parameters.Actually, looking at the error message more carefully: \"缺少必需的查询参数: 'category'\" - it says \"查询参数\" which literally means \"query parameter\". Maybe QVeris expects parameters differently - maybe as URL query parameters, not in the request body?\n\nLet me look at the API more carefully. The tool definition shows parameters but maybe they're meant to be passed differently. Let me try the API with a tool that I know works and see what the difference is.\n\nActually, I think the issue may be that some tools require parameters to be passed as query parameters to the underlying API, but QVeris is not correctly mapping them. Let me try a different approach - fetch financial news directly from Finnhub's public API.","thinkingSignature":"703c8756e1b839df119658850355809322ff09ff92a0c4173309b0350efcb015"},{"type":"text","text":"Since QVeris has parameter passing issues, let me try getting Finnhub news directly:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vmv8g1f049x7_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s \"https://finnhub.io/api/v1/news?category=general&token=$FINNHUB_API_KEY\" | head -c 3000","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":30140,"output":269,"cacheRead":13984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44393,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772532264582}}
