{"type":"message","id":"c3b40e8a","parentId":"78c95946","timestamp":"2026-03-03T10:05:27.596Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_lnrfvrsjq0ev_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"execution_id\": \"f5fde697-f6dc-4e35-a9ae-f346782ad7bf\",\n  \"result\": {\n    \"status_code\": 200,\n    \"message\": \"Result content is too long (232901 bytes). You can reference the truncated content (20480 bytes) and download the full content from the url provided.\",\n    \"full_content_file_url\": \"http://qveris-tool-results-cache-bj.oss-cn-beijing.aliyuncs.com/tool_result_cache%2F20260303%2Feodhd.news.retrieve.v1.fe8bf94c%2F20641bc34b534ea0979522c92aeb7852.json?OSSAccessKeyId=LTAI5tM3qNRZSgSrg1iSTALm&Expires=1772539526&Signature=JRmsJ2V9IshbjbxUVi5bklwQSD0%3D\",\n    \"truncated_content\": \"[{\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-03T10:03:00+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Is $71K New Ceiling for Bitcoin? Analyst Decodes Latest BTC Technical Setup\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"Well-known trader Cred, creator of the Technical Roundup channel, shared on X his updated view on Bitcoin’s price today, outlining what he sees as the defining level for BTC in the current market structure. According to him, $71,000 now stands as the most important threshold, effectively framing the next major directional move.\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://u.today/is-71k-new-ceiling-for-bitcoin-analyst-decodes-latest-btc-technical-setup\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [\\\"ARDR-USD.CC\\\", \\\"BTC-USD.US\\\"], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"BITCOIN\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": 0.769, \\\"neg\\\": 0, \\\"neu\\\": 0.86, \\\"pos\\\": 0.14}}, {\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-03T09:54:33+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Trending tickers: MongoDB, Thales, Fresnillo, Greggs and Inchcape\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"MongoDB (MDB)\\\\n\\\\nShares in software company MongoDB (MDB) was down 25% in pre-market trading on Tuesday, after the firm forecast a loss for the year ahead.\\\\n\\\\nIn fourth quarter results released on Monday, MongoDB said it expected to report a loss per share of $0.73 (£0.54) to $0.49 for the 2027 fiscal year. However, this was lower than the $1.05 loss Wall Street was expecting, according to S&P Global Market Intelligence.\\\\n\\\\nRead more: London stocks hit new low amid Middle East crisis\\\\n\\\\nThe company said it expected revenue to land between $2.86bn and $2.90bn, compared to estimates for $2.43bn.\\\\n\\\\nFor the fourth quarter, MongoDB reported net income per share of $0.19 on revenue of $695.1m. For the year, the company posted a loss per share of $0.88 on revenue of $2.46bn.\\\\n\\\\nNasdaqGM - Delayed Quote•USD\\\\n\\\\n(MDB)\\\\n\\\\nFollow  View Quote Details\\\\n\\\\n325.01 -3.46 (-1.05%)\\\\n\\\\nAt close: March 2 at 4:00:03 PM EST  Advanced Chart\\\\n\\\\nThales (HO.PA)\\\\n\\\\nIn Europe, Paris-listed aerospace and technology company Thales (HO.PA) reported profit for the year that came in slightly ahead of expectations on Tuesday.\\\\n\\\\nThales posted adjusted earning before interest and taxes (EBIT) of €2.74bn (£2.39bn) for 2025, which was 14% higher than the previous year on an organic basis and beat expectations of €2.69bn, according to consensus estimates provided by the company.\\\\n\\\\nThe firm reported 1% growth in its order intake at €25.26bn for the year, compared to estimates of €25.21bn. Meanwhile, sales totalled €22.14bn, up 9% on 2024, though this was slightly below expectations of €21.88bn.\\\\n\\\\nShares in the company dipped 1.7% in early European trading on Tuesday but are up more than 15% over one year.\\\\n\\\\nParis - Delayed Quote•USD\\\\n\\\\n(HO.PA)\\\\n\\\\nFollow  View Quote Details\\\\n\\\\n252.00 -3.90 (-1.52%)\\\\n\\\\nAs of 10:41:26 AM GMT+1. Market Open.  Advanced Chart\\\\n\\\\nFresnillo (FRES.L)\\\\n\\\\nOn the UK's FTSE 100 (^FTSE), shares in precious metals miner Fresnillo (FRES.L) slipped 3.7% lower on Tuesday morning, after reported annual falls in silver and gold production in its results.\\\\n\\\\nFresnillo said that silver production had fallen 13.5% in 2025, while gold output declined 5% in the year.\\\\n\\\\nEven so, the company reported 30.5% growth in revenue to $4.56bn , while profit for the year soared 594% to $1.57bn.\\\\n\\\\nStocks: Create your watchlist and portfolio\\\\n\\\\nAdam Vettese, market analyst for eToro, said: \\\\\\\"Fresnillo’s results are a triumph of price over production, delivering record earnings amid the silver bull market.\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\nHowever, he said that \\\\\\\"beneath the gloss, volumes tell a tougher story\\\\\\\".\\\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\"Cost controls shone, but mine challenges persist, from grades at Fresnillo to the Silverstream termination loss,\\\\\\\" Vettese said.\\\\n\\\\nLSE - Delayed Quote•USD\\\\n\\\\n(FRES.L)\\\\n\\\\nFollow  View Quote Details\\\\n\\\\n3,924.53 -195.47 (-4.74%)\\\\n\\\\nAs of 9:41:39 AM GMT. Market Open.  Advanced Chart\\\\n\\\\nGreggs (GRG.L)\\\\n\\\\nOn the FTSE 250 (^FTMC), shares in bakery chain Greggs (GRG.L) edged nearly 1% lower, after the company reported a fall in annual profits amid a slowdown in sales growth over the start of the new year.\\\\n\\\\nStory Continues\\\\n\\\\nGreggs posted 6.8% growth in total sales for 2025 at £2.15bn ($2.85bn), but underlying profit before tax declined 9.4% to £171.9m.\\\\n\\\\nRead more: What to expect from Rachel Reeves' spring statement\\\\n\\\\nChris Beauchamp, chief market analyst at IG, said: \\\\\\\"Greggs has picked a bad moment to release results, just as a surge in energy prices raises fears of renewed inflation.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\"The company's hopes that sales will recover later in the year increasingly looks like pie in the sky, especially since it seems set on continued expansion.\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\"This will either turn out to be a brilliant long-term move, or an imprudent decision from a business facing threats on multiple fronts,\\\\\\\" he said. \\\\\\\"Only time will tell.\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\nLSE - Delayed Quote•USD\\\\n\\\\n(GRG.L)\\\\n\\\\nFollow  View Quote Details\\\\n\\\\n1,558.42 -12.58 (-0.80%)\\\\n\\\\nAs of 9:41:25 AM GMT. Market Open.  Advanced Chart\\\\n\\\\nInchcape (INCH.L)\\\\n\\\\nAutomotive distribution company Inchcape (INCH.L) was the biggest faller on the FTSE 250 on Tuesday morning, with shares down 8.6% at the time of writing.\\\\n\\\\nIn its annual results on Tuesday, Inchcape reported 1% growth in revenue for the year at £9.1bn, while adjusted profit before tax was little changed from the previous year at £443m.\\\\n\\\\nRead more: Stocks that are trending today\\\\n\\\\nDuncan Tait, group CEO of Inchcape, said: \\\\\\\"During a transformative year in the automotive sector in FY 2025, Inchcape's diversified and scaled business model delivered results in line with our medium-term targets, reporting double-digit EPS [earnings per share] growth.\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\"Looking ahead, we expect to deliver a year of growth in FY 2026, including adjusted EPS growth of >10%, with volume growth, resilient margins, supported by strong execution and discipline on costs, and cash conversion,\\\\\\\" he said.\\\\n\\\\nThe drop in shares came despite Inchcape announcing a new £175m share buyback programme.\\\\n\\\\nRead more:\\\\n\\\\nWhy more Britons are carrying mortgages into retirement and how to prepare for it How to save on income tax Stocks to watch this week: Broadcom, Costco, Adidas, Aviva and Greggs\\\\n\\\\nDownload the Yahoo Finance app, available for Apple andAndroid.\\\\n\\\\nView Comments\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://uk.finance.yahoo.com/news/mongodb-thales-fresnillo-greggs-inchcape-trending-tickers-095433859.html\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [\\\"FRES.LSE\\\", \\\"FRES.MX\\\", \\\"FRES.US\\\", \\\"GRG.LSE\\\", \\\"GRG.US\\\", \\\"HO.PA\\\", \\\"INCH.US\\\", \\\"MDB.US\\\"], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"AEROSPACE\\\", \\\"EARNINGS\\\", \\\"EARNINGS PER SHARE\\\", \\\"FOURTH QUARTER\\\", \\\"NET INCOME\\\", \\\"PRECIOUS-METALS\\\", \\\"PRICE-TARGET\\\", \\\"RETAIL\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": 0.997, \\\"neg\\\": 0.047, \\\"neu\\\": 0.821, \\\"pos\\\": 0.132}}, {\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-03T09:53:00+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"MXene Industry Research Report 2026: Market to Grow at a CAGR of 35.6% to 2032, Driven by EV &amp; Charging Infrastructure, Water Treatment Applications and High-Performance Aerospace &amp; Defense Systems\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"Company Logo\\\\n\\\\nThe global MXene market, valued at USD 0.05 billion in 2026, is anticipated to reach USD 0.29 billion by 2032, experiencing a CAGR of 35.6%. The growth is driven by demand for high-performance 2D materials with superior electrical conductivity and mechanical strength, crucial for sectors like energy storage and electronics as traditional materials reach their limits. Key production methods, including electrochemical etching, offer high purity and scalability. Powder form MXenes, compatible with various manufacturing processes, dominate market growth. China leads the Asia Pacific market with a strong manufacturing base and government support. Major players include Beijing Beike, Merck, and XFNANO. The report offers insights into market drivers, opportunities in energy storage, and competitive developments.\\\\n\\\\nDublin, March 03, 2026 (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) -- The \\\\\\\"MXene Market by Type, Production Method, Form, End User, and Region - Global Forecast to 2032\\\\\\\" report has been added to  ResearchAndMarkets.com's offering.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nThe global MXene market is valued at USD 0.05 billion in 2026 and is projected to reach USD 0.29 billion by 2032, registering a CAGR of 35.6%\\\\n\\\\nThe report will help market leaders/new entrants with information on the closest approximations of the revenue for the overall MXene market and its subsegments. The report will help stakeholders understand the competitive landscape and gain more insight to position their business better and plan suitable go-to-market strategies. The report also helps stakeholders understand the market's pulse and provides information on key drivers, restraints, opportunities, and challenges.\\\\n\\\\nThe MXene market is advancing rapidly due to rising demand for high performance two dimensional materials. These materials offer strong electrical conductivity and mechanical strength. Surface tunability supports application specific customization. Industries such as energy storage and electronics require higher efficiency. Electromagnetic interference shielding and sensors also drive demand. Conventional materials are reaching performance limits.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nMXenes provide an advanced alternative for compact system design. Faster charge transport improves device efficiency. Higher energy density supports improved performance. Functional integration enables system level optimization. Surface engineering improves reliability across use cases. These advantages support adoption in next generation applications. MXenes enable commercial scalability. They also align with long term technological objectives across industries.\\\\n\\\\nStory Continues\\\\n\\\\nChina is expected to hold the largest share of the Asia Pacific MXene market in 2025 due to its strong nanomaterials manufacturing base. The country has an advanced research ecosystem supporting material innovation. A high concentration of academic institutions is active in MXene synthesis. Industrial players are also engaged in application development.\\\\n\\\\nLarge scale investment in energy storage is supporting demand. Electronics manufacturing further strengthens adoption. Electromagnetic shielding technologies add another growth area. Government support for advanced materials accelerates commercialization. Early adoption enables faster scale up of production. These factors position China as the leading MXene market in the Asia Pacific region.\\\\n\\\\nProminent players profiled in this report include Beijing Beike New Material Technology (China), Merck (Germany), Alfa Chemistry (US), American Elements (US), XFNANO (China), Japan Material Technologies Corporation (Japan), ACS Material, LLC (US), 2D Semiconductors (US), Otto Chemie Pvt. Ltd. (US), SixCarbon Technology (China).\\\\n\\\\nElectrochemical etching, by production method is expected to grow at the fastest CAGR during the forecast period.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nElectrochemical etching is expected to grow at the fastest CAGR during the forecast period due to higher material purity and improved structural control. Reduced use of hazardous chemicals supports safer production. The method enables precise layer by layer etching.\\\\n\\\\nThis results in MXenes with uniform morphology. Consistent electrochemical properties improve reliability. Electrochemical etching supports scalable manufacturing. Cost efficiency aligns with industrial production needs. Sustainable processing supports long term adoption. Large scale commercialization of MXene based solutions benefits from this method.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nPowder form MXene is expected to dominate market growth during the forecast period\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nDemand for MXene powder is rising due to its versatility across end use applications and compatibility with established manufacturing processes. Powdered MXene disperses easily into polymers, inks, slurries. This supports large scale production of electrodes and coatings. Functional composites also benefit from this format.\\\\n\\\\nHigh surface area improves electrical conductivity. Tunable surface chemistry enhances electrochemical performance. These properties support energy storage and shielding applications. Powder form simplifies transportation and storage. Formulation becomes more efficient. Processing complexity is reduced. Overall production costs are lower.\\\\n\\\\nMarket Dynamics\\\\n\\\\nDrivers\\\\n\\\\nRising Emphasis on High-Performance Energy Storage Solutions Thriving Electronics and Semiconductor Manufacturing Industries Increasing Need for Electromagnetic Interference (Emi) Shielding Mounting Adoption of Advanced Nanomaterials in Medical Diagnostics and Sensing Applications\\\\n\\\\nRestraints\\\\n\\\\nManufacturing Limitations and Absence of Standardized Protocols Long-Term Performance and Data Reliability Constraints\\\\n\\\\nOpportunities\\\\n\\\\nIntegration into Electric Vehicles and Charging Infrastructure Usage in Water Treatment and Environmental Remediation Requirement for High-Performance Materials in Aerospace and Defense Systems\\\\n\\\\nChallenges\\\\n\\\\nIssues in Achieving Consistent Material Quality Across Production Batches Challenges in Integrating Mxenes into Established Manufacturing Processes\\\\n\\\\nTechnological Advancements, AI-Driven Impacts, Patents, and Innovations\\\\n\\\\nKey Technologies\\\\n\\\\nMxene Synthesis and Processing Surface Functionalization and Material Integration\\\\n\\\\nComplementary Technologies\\\\n\\\\nComposite Materials and Hybrid Systems Advanced Modeling and Simulation\\\\n\\\\nAdjacent Technologies\\\\n\\\\nAdvanced Energy Storage Advanced Materials and Nanotechnology Platforms\\\\n\\\\nTechnology Roadmap\\\\n\\\\nPatent Analysis\\\\n\\\\nImpact of AI on Mxene Market\\\\n\\\\nTop Use Cases and Market Potential Clients' Readiness to Adopt AI-Integrated Mxene Solutions\\\\n\\\\nRegulatory Landscape\\\\n\\\\nRegional Regulations and Compliance Regulatory Bodies, Government Agencies, and Other Organizations Industry Standards Regulations\\\\n\\\\nCompanies Featured\\\\n\\\\nBeijing Beike New Material Technology Co. Ltd Merck KGaA Alfa Chemistry American Elements Xfnano Japan Material Technologies Corporation (Jmtc) Acs Material 2D Semiconductors Otto Chemie Pvt. Ltd Sixcarbon Technology (Shenzhen) Mxenenanotech LLC Aritech Chemazone Pvt. Ltd. Nanoshel LLC Sat Nano Technology Material Co. Ltd. Nanografi Cheap Tubes Nanorh Shanghai Heqi Chemical Technology Co. Ltd. Epoch Material Nanocarbontech Nanoplexus Mxene Nanomxene Mse Supplies LLC Nanjing Jicang Nanotechnology Co. Ltd.\\\\n\\\\nFor more information about this report visit https://www.researchandmarkets.com/r/vdg3lb\\\\n\\\\nAbout ResearchAndMarkets.com\\\\r\\\\nResearchAndMarkets.com is the world's leading source for international market research reports and market data. We provide you with the latest data on international and regional markets, key industries, the top companies, new products and the latest trends.\\\\n\\\\nCONTACT: CONTACT: ResearchAndMarkets.com Laura Wood,Senior Press Manager press@researchandmarkets.com For E.S.T Office Hours Call 1-917-300-0470 For U.S./ CAN Toll Free Call 1-800-526-8630 For GMT Office Hours Call +353-1-416-8900\\\\n\\\\nView Comments\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/mxene-industry-research-report-2026-095300271.html\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [\\\"MRK.US\\\"], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"ELECTROMAGNETIC-SHIELDING\\\", \\\"ELECTRONICS\\\", \\\"ENERGY-STORAGE\\\", \\\"MARKET RESEARCH REPORTS\\\", \\\"MXENE\\\", \\\"NANOMATERIALS\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": 1, \\\"neg\\\": 0.011, \\\"neu\\\": 0.799, \\\"pos\\\": 0.19}}, {\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-03T09:50:00+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Better Buy in 2026: Bitcoin or a Broad-Market ETF? The Answer Couldn't Be Clearer for Long-Term Investors\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"Cryptocurrency prices, including Bitcoin (CRYPTO: BTC), have been pummeled during the past few months as investors have rotated out of more speculative investments to safer ones. With the threat of tariffs rearing their ugly head again and investors concerned about how artificial intelligence (AI) might disrupt established companies and industries, desire to own digital currencies is on the wane.\\\\n\\\\nThe result is that Bitcoin has tumbled, and I think there's a case for investors to put their money into a broad-market exchange-traded fund (ETF) right now. The Vanguard S&P 500 ETF(NYSEMKT: VOO) is my personal favorite. Here's why it's a better buy than Bitcoin this year.\\\\n\\\\nWill AI create the world's first trillionaire? Our team just released a report on the one little-known company, called an \\\\\\\"Indispensable Monopoly\\\\\\\" providing the critical technology Nvidia and Intel both need. Continue »Image source: Getty Images.\\\\n\\\\nRisky investments are losing their appeal\\\\n\\\\nIt wasn't all that long ago that investors had a seemingly insatiable appetite for riskier investments. Consider that Bitcoin's price reached its all-time high of more than $126,500 in October, before the recent crypto sell-off caused its price to plummet to about $69,000 as of this writing.\\\\n\\\\nThere isn't one single factor that's caused the retreat, but rather a general skepticism about some AI stocks, uncertainty about where the economy is headed amid geopolitical uncertainties, and President Donald Trump announcing new global tariffs of as much as 15% -- just after the Supreme Court struck down his previous round of tariffs.\\\\n\\\\nAdditionally, layoffs in January were the highest in that month in 17 years, and the World Economic Forum said recently that 41% of global companies are expecting to reduce their staff during the next five years because of artificial intelligence.\\\\n\\\\nBitcoin had been on a tear in a post-COVID world where tech stocks were soaring, and initial AI optimism helped lift digital currency prices. But now some investors have the sense that economic winds might be shifting, and they have pared back on Bitcoin, along with many other cryptocurrencies and other speculative investments, including quantum computing stocks.Source: YCharts.\\\\n\\\\nBoring looks beautiful right now\\\\n\\\\nWhile Bitcoin is down about 23% during the past year, the Vanguard S&P 500 ETF has been slowly and steadily climbing more than 16%.\\\\n\\\\nThe fund tracks the S&P 500, so if the market is doing well, the fund tends to perform well too. The benefit of having your money spread across the largest 500 publicly traded companies in the U.S. is that you have the potential to benefit from many areas of growth, including AI, healthcare, consumer spending, industrial production, and more.\\\\n\\\\nStory Continues\\\\n\\\\nThis strategy has, historically, been a very good one. Since the fund's inception in 2010, it has had an annual average return of 14.8%. There's no guarantee you will receive those returns in any given year, of course, but it does show that the fund's diversification can lead to impressive returns when various economic sectors are doing well.\\\\n\\\\nSome investors don't like passive ETF investing and want the ability to personally select stocks and cryptos for their portfolio. I understand the appeal, and there's nothing wrong with that strategy. But it becomes difficult when, as now, the direction of the economy and many in dustries is hazy.\\\\n\\\\nThat's why buying this Vanguard ETF makes sense right now. While other investors try to figure out which sectors and companies will benefit or be dismantled by AI, or how tariffs will affect industrial companies in the coming years, you can instead put your money into a fund that spreads out your investments into a basket of stocks.\\\\n\\\\nNot only will you be well diversified, but you also will pay a very low annual expense ratio of just 0.03%, compared to the average S&P 500 fund fee of 0.41%.That means for every $1,000 invested in the fund, you will pay just $0.30 annually.\\\\n\\\\nI don't think Bitcoin is a bad investment, but with 2026 already off to an uncertain start, loading up on the Vanguard S&P 500 ETF may look like a wise move several years from now.\\\\n\\\\nShould you buy stock in Bitcoin right now?\\\\n\\\\nBefore you buy stock in Bitcoin, consider this:\\\\n\\\\nThe Motley Fool Stock Advisor analyst team just identified what they believe are the 10 best stocks for investors to buy now… and Bitcoin wasn’t one of them. The 10 stocks that made the cut could produce monster returns in the coming years.\\\\n\\\\nConsider when Netflix made this list on December 17, 2004... if you invested $1,000 at the time of our recommendation, you’d have $519,015!* Or when Nvidia made this list on April 15, 2005... if you invested $1,000 at the time of our recommendation, you’d have $1,086,211!*\\\\n\\\\nNow, it’s worth noting Stock Advisor’s total average return is 941% — a market-crushing outperformance compared to 194% for the S&P 500. Don't miss the latest top 10 list, available with Stock Advisor, and join an investing community built by individual investors for individual investors.\\\\n\\\\nSee the 10 stocks »\\\\n\\\\n*Stock Advisor returns as of March 3, 2026.\\\\n\\\\nChris Neiger has positions in Vanguard S&P 500 ETF. The Mo\",\n    \"content_schema\": {\n      \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/schema#\",\n      \"type\": \"array\",\n      \"items\": {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"date\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"title\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"content\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"link\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"symbols\": {\n            \"type\": \"array\",\n            \"items\": {\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            }\n          },\n          \"tags\": {\n            \"type\": \"array\",\n            \"items\": {\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            }\n          },\n          \"sentiment\": {\n            \"type\": \"object\",\n            \"properties\": {\n              \"polarity\": {\n                \"type\": \"number\"\n              },\n              \"neg\": {\n                \"type\": \"number\"\n              },\n              \"neu\": {\n                \"type\": \"number\"\n              },\n              \"pos\": {\n                \"type\": \"number\"\n              }\n            },\n            \"required\": [\n              \"neg\",\n              \"neu\",\n              \"polarity\",\n              \"pos\"\n            ]\n          }\n        },\n        \"required\": [\n          \"content\",\n          \"date\",\n          \"link\",\n          \"sentiment\",\n          \"symbols\",\n          \"tags\",\n          \"title\"\n        ]\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"elapsed_time_ms\": 1737.72,\n  \"cost\": 6.5\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":3695,"aggregated":"{\n  \"execution_id\": \"f5fde697-f6dc-4e35-a9ae-f346782ad7bf\",\n  \"result\": {\n    \"status_code\": 200,\n    \"message\": \"Result content is too long (232901 bytes). You can reference the truncated content (20480 bytes) and download the full content from the url provided.\",\n    \"full_content_file_url\": \"http://qveris-tool-results-cache-bj.oss-cn-beijing.aliyuncs.com/tool_result_cache%2F20260303%2Feodhd.news.retrieve.v1.fe8bf94c%2F20641bc34b534ea0979522c92aeb7852.json?OSSAccessKeyId=LTAI5tM3qNRZSgSrg1iSTALm&Expires=1772539526&Signature=JRmsJ2V9IshbjbxUVi5bklwQSD0%3D\",\n    \"truncated_content\": \"[{\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-03T10:03:00+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Is $71K New Ceiling for Bitcoin? Analyst Decodes Latest BTC Technical Setup\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"Well-known trader Cred, creator of the Technical Roundup channel, shared on X his updated view on Bitcoin’s price today, outlining what he sees as the defining level for BTC in the current market structure. According to him, $71,000 now stands as the most important threshold, effectively framing the next major directional move.\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://u.today/is-71k-new-ceiling-for-bitcoin-analyst-decodes-latest-btc-technical-setup\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [\\\"ARDR-USD.CC\\\", \\\"BTC-USD.US\\\"], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"BITCOIN\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": 0.769, \\\"neg\\\": 0, \\\"neu\\\": 0.86, \\\"pos\\\": 0.14}}, {\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-03T09:54:33+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Trending tickers: MongoDB, Thales, Fresnillo, Greggs and Inchcape\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"MongoDB (MDB)\\\\n\\\\nShares in software company MongoDB (MDB) was down 25% in pre-market trading on Tuesday, after the firm forecast a loss for the year ahead.\\\\n\\\\nIn fourth quarter results released on Monday, MongoDB said it expected to report a loss per share of $0.73 (£0.54) to $0.49 for the 2027 fiscal year. However, this was lower than the $1.05 loss Wall Street was expecting, according to S&P Global Market Intelligence.\\\\n\\\\nRead more: London stocks hit new low amid Middle East crisis\\\\n\\\\nThe company said it expected revenue to land between $2.86bn and $2.90bn, compared to estimates for $2.43bn.\\\\n\\\\nFor the fourth quarter, MongoDB reported net income per share of $0.19 on revenue of $695.1m. For the year, the company posted a loss per share of $0.88 on revenue of $2.46bn.\\\\n\\\\nNasdaqGM - Delayed Quote•USD\\\\n\\\\n(MDB)\\\\n\\\\nFollow  View Quote Details\\\\n\\\\n325.01 -3.46 (-1.05%)\\\\n\\\\nAt close: March 2 at 4:00:03 PM EST  Advanced Chart\\\\n\\\\nThales (HO.PA)\\\\n\\\\nIn Europe, Paris-listed aerospace and technology company Thales (HO.PA) reported profit for the year that came in slightly ahead of expectations on Tuesday.\\\\n\\\\nThales posted adjusted earning before interest and taxes (EBIT) of €2.74bn (£2.39bn) for 2025, which was 14% higher than the previous year on an organic basis and beat expectations of €2.69bn, according to consensus estimates provided by the company.\\\\n\\\\nThe firm reported 1% growth in its order intake at €25.26bn for the year, compared to estimates of €25.21bn. Meanwhile, sales totalled €22.14bn, up 9% on 2024, though this was slightly below expectations of €21.88bn.\\\\n\\\\nShares in the company dipped 1.7% in early European trading on Tuesday but are up more than 15% over one year.\\\\n\\\\nParis - Delayed Quote•USD\\\\n\\\\n(HO.PA)\\\\n\\\\nFollow  View Quote Details\\\\n\\\\n252.00 -3.90 (-1.52%)\\\\n\\\\nAs of 10:41:26 AM GMT+1. Market Open.  Advanced Chart\\\\n\\\\nFresnillo (FRES.L)\\\\n\\\\nOn the UK's FTSE 100 (^FTSE), shares in precious metals miner Fresnillo (FRES.L) slipped 3.7% lower on Tuesday morning, after reported annual falls in silver and gold production in its results.\\\\n\\\\nFresnillo said that silver production had fallen 13.5% in 2025, while gold output declined 5% in the year.\\\\n\\\\nEven so, the company reported 30.5% growth in revenue to $4.56bn , while profit for the year soared 594% to $1.57bn.\\\\n\\\\nStocks: Create your watchlist and portfolio\\\\n\\\\nAdam Vettese, market analyst for eToro, said: \\\\\\\"Fresnillo’s results are a triumph of price over production, delivering record earnings amid the silver bull market.\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\nHowever, he said that \\\\\\\"beneath the gloss, volumes tell a tougher story\\\\\\\".\\\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\"Cost controls shone, but mine challenges persist, from grades at Fresnillo to the Silverstream termination loss,\\\\\\\" Vettese said.\\\\n\\\\nLSE - Delayed Quote•USD\\\\n\\\\n(FRES.L)\\\\n\\\\nFollow  View Quote Details\\\\n\\\\n3,924.53 -195.47 (-4.74%)\\\\n\\\\nAs of 9:41:39 AM GMT. Market Open.  Advanced Chart\\\\n\\\\nGreggs (GRG.L)\\\\n\\\\nOn the FTSE 250 (^FTMC), shares in bakery chain Greggs (GRG.L) edged nearly 1% lower, after the company reported a fall in annual profits amid a slowdown in sales growth over the start of the new year.\\\\n\\\\nStory Continues\\\\n\\\\nGreggs posted 6.8% growth in total sales for 2025 at £2.15bn ($2.85bn), but underlying profit before tax declined 9.4% to £171.9m.\\\\n\\\\nRead more: What to expect from Rachel Reeves' spring statement\\\\n\\\\nChris Beauchamp, chief market analyst at IG, said: \\\\\\\"Greggs has picked a bad moment to release results, just as a surge in energy prices raises fears of renewed inflation.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\"The company's hopes that sales will recover later in the year increasingly looks like pie in the sky, especially since it seems set on continued expansion.\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\"This will either turn out to be a brilliant long-term move, or an imprudent decision from a business facing threats on multiple fronts,\\\\\\\" he said. \\\\\\\"Only time will tell.\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\nLSE - Delayed Quote•USD\\\\n\\\\n(GRG.L)\\\\n\\\\nFollow  View Quote Details\\\\n\\\\n1,558.42 -12.58 (-0.80%)\\\\n\\\\nAs of 9:41:25 AM GMT. Market Open.  Advanced Chart\\\\n\\\\nInchcape (INCH.L)\\\\n\\\\nAutomotive distribution company Inchcape (INCH.L) was the biggest faller on the FTSE 250 on Tuesday morning, with shares down 8.6% at the time of writing.\\\\n\\\\nIn its annual results on Tuesday, Inchcape reported 1% growth in revenue for the year at £9.1bn, while adjusted profit before tax was little changed from the previous year at £443m.\\\\n\\\\nRead more: Stocks that are trending today\\\\n\\\\nDuncan Tait, group CEO of Inchcape, said: \\\\\\\"During a transformative year in the automotive sector in FY 2025, Inchcape's diversified and scaled business model delivered results in line with our medium-term targets, reporting double-digit EPS [earnings per share] growth.\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\"Looking ahead, we expect to deliver a year of growth in FY 2026, including adjusted EPS growth of >10%, with volume growth, resilient margins, supported by strong execution and discipline on costs, and cash conversion,\\\\\\\" he said.\\\\n\\\\nThe drop in shares came despite Inchcape announcing a new £175m share buyback programme.\\\\n\\\\nRead more:\\\\n\\\\nWhy more Britons are carrying mortgages into retirement and how to prepare for it How to save on income tax Stocks to watch this week: Broadcom, Costco, Adidas, Aviva and Greggs\\\\n\\\\nDownload the Yahoo Finance app, available for Apple andAndroid.\\\\n\\\\nView Comments\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://uk.finance.yahoo.com/news/mongodb-thales-fresnillo-greggs-inchcape-trending-tickers-095433859.html\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [\\\"FRES.LSE\\\", \\\"FRES.MX\\\", \\\"FRES.US\\\", \\\"GRG.LSE\\\", \\\"GRG.US\\\", \\\"HO.PA\\\", \\\"INCH.US\\\", \\\"MDB.US\\\"], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"AEROSPACE\\\", \\\"EARNINGS\\\", \\\"EARNINGS PER SHARE\\\", \\\"FOURTH QUARTER\\\", \\\"NET INCOME\\\", \\\"PRECIOUS-METALS\\\", \\\"PRICE-TARGET\\\", \\\"RETAIL\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": 0.997, \\\"neg\\\": 0.047, \\\"neu\\\": 0.821, \\\"pos\\\": 0.132}}, {\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-03T09:53:00+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"MXene Industry Research Report 2026: Market to Grow at a CAGR of 35.6% to 2032, Driven by EV &amp; Charging Infrastructure, Water Treatment Applications and High-Performance Aerospace &amp; Defense Systems\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"Company Logo\\\\n\\\\nThe global MXene market, valued at USD 0.05 billion in 2026, is anticipated to reach USD 0.29 billion by 2032, experiencing a CAGR of 35.6%. The growth is driven by demand for high-performance 2D materials with superior electrical conductivity and mechanical strength, crucial for sectors like energy storage and electronics as traditional materials reach their limits. Key production methods, including electrochemical etching, offer high purity and scalability. Powder form MXenes, compatible with various manufacturing processes, dominate market growth. China leads the Asia Pacific market with a strong manufacturing base and government support. Major players include Beijing Beike, Merck, and XFNANO. The report offers insights into market drivers, opportunities in energy storage, and competitive developments.\\\\n\\\\nDublin, March 03, 2026 (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) -- The \\\\\\\"MXene Market by Type, Production Method, Form, End User, and Region - Global Forecast to 2032\\\\\\\" report has been added to  ResearchAndMarkets.com's offering.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nThe global MXene market is valued at USD 0.05 billion in 2026 and is projected to reach USD 0.29 billion by 2032, registering a CAGR of 35.6%\\\\n\\\\nThe report will help market leaders/new entrants with information on the closest approximations of the revenue for the overall MXene market and its subsegments. The report will help stakeholders understand the competitive landscape and gain more insight to position their business better and plan suitable go-to-market strategies. The report also helps stakeholders understand the market's pulse and provides information on key drivers, restraints, opportunities, and challenges.\\\\n\\\\nThe MXene market is advancing rapidly due to rising demand for high performance two dimensional materials. These materials offer strong electrical conductivity and mechanical strength. Surface tunability supports application specific customization. Industries such as energy storage and electronics require higher efficiency. Electromagnetic interference shielding and sensors also drive demand. Conventional materials are reaching performance limits.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nMXenes provide an advanced alternative for compact system design. Faster charge transport improves device efficiency. Higher energy density supports improved performance. Functional integration enables system level optimization. Surface engineering improves reliability across use cases. These advantages support adoption in next generation applications. MXenes enable commercial scalability. They also align with long term technological objectives across industries.\\\\n\\\\nStory Continues\\\\n\\\\nChina is expected to hold the largest share of the Asia Pacific MXene market in 2025 due to its strong nanomaterials manufacturing base. The country has an advanced research ecosystem supporting material innovation. A high concentration of academic institutions is active in MXene synthesis. Industrial players are also engaged in application development.\\\\n\\\\nLarge scale investment in energy storage is supporting demand. Electronics manufacturing further strengthens adoption. Electromagnetic shielding technologies add another growth area. Government support for advanced materials accelerates commercialization. Early adoption enables faster scale up of production. These factors position China as the leading MXene market in the Asia Pacific region.\\\\n\\\\nProminent players profiled in this report include Beijing Beike New Material Technology (China), Merck (Germany), Alfa Chemistry (US), American Elements (US), XFNANO (China), Japan Material Technologies Corporation (Japan), ACS Material, LLC (US), 2D Semiconductors (US), Otto Chemie Pvt. Ltd. (US), SixCarbon Technology (China).\\\\n\\\\nElectrochemical etching, by production method is expected to grow at the fastest CAGR during the forecast period.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nElectrochemical etching is expected to grow at the fastest CAGR during the forecast period due to higher material purity and improved structural control. Reduced use of hazardous chemicals supports safer production. The method enables precise layer by layer etching.\\\\n\\\\nThis results in MXenes with uniform morphology. Consistent electrochemical properties improve reliability. Electrochemical etching supports scalable manufacturing. Cost efficiency aligns with industrial production needs. Sustainable processing supports long term adoption. Large scale commercialization of MXene based solutions benefits from this method.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nPowder form MXene is expected to dominate market growth during the forecast period\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nDemand for MXene powder is rising due to its versatility across end use applications and compatibility with established manufacturing processes. Powdered MXene disperses easily into polymers, inks, slurries. This supports large scale production of electrodes and coatings. Functional composites also benefit from this format.\\\\n\\\\nHigh surface area improves electrical conductivity. Tunable surface chemistry enhances electrochemical performance. These properties support energy storage and shielding applications. Powder form simplifies transportation and storage. Formulation becomes more efficient. Processing complexity is reduced. Overall production costs are lower.\\\\n\\\\nMarket Dynamics\\\\n\\\\nDrivers\\\\n\\\\nRising Emphasis on High-Performance Energy Storage Solutions Thriving Electronics and Semiconductor Manufacturing Industries Increasing Need for Electromagnetic Interference (Emi) Shielding Mounting Adoption of Advanced Nanomaterials in Medical Diagnostics and Sensing Applications\\\\n\\\\nRestraints\\\\n\\\\nManufacturing Limitations and Absence of Standardized Protocols Long-Term Performance and Data Reliability Constraints\\\\n\\\\nOpportunities\\\\n\\\\nIntegration into Electric Vehicles and Charging Infrastructure Usage in Water Treatment and Environmental Remediation Requirement for High-Performance Materials in Aerospace and Defense Systems\\\\n\\\\nChallenges\\\\n\\\\nIssues in Achieving Consistent Material Quality Across Production Batches Challenges in Integrating Mxenes into Established Manufacturing Processes\\\\n\\\\nTechnological Advancements, AI-Driven Impacts, Patents, and Innovations\\\\n\\\\nKey Technologies\\\\n\\\\nMxene Synthesis and Processing Surface Functionalization and Material Integration\\\\n\\\\nComplementary Technologies\\\\n\\\\nComposite Materials and Hybrid Systems Advanced Modeling and Simulation\\\\n\\\\nAdjacent Technologies\\\\n\\\\nAdvanced Energy Storage Advanced Materials and Nanotechnology Platforms\\\\n\\\\nTechnology Roadmap\\\\n\\\\nPatent Analysis\\\\n\\\\nImpact of AI on Mxene Market\\\\n\\\\nTop Use Cases and Market Potential Clients' Readiness to Adopt AI-Integrated Mxene Solutions\\\\n\\\\nRegulatory Landscape\\\\n\\\\nRegional Regulations and Compliance Regulatory Bodies, Government Agencies, and Other Organizations Industry Standards Regulations\\\\n\\\\nCompanies Featured\\\\n\\\\nBeijing Beike New Material Technology Co. Ltd Merck KGaA Alfa Chemistry American Elements Xfnano Japan Material Technologies Corporation (Jmtc) Acs Material 2D Semiconductors Otto Chemie Pvt. Ltd Sixcarbon Technology (Shenzhen) Mxenenanotech LLC Aritech Chemazone Pvt. Ltd. Nanoshel LLC Sat Nano Technology Material Co. Ltd. Nanografi Cheap Tubes Nanorh Shanghai Heqi Chemical Technology Co. Ltd. Epoch Material Nanocarbontech Nanoplexus Mxene Nanomxene Mse Supplies LLC Nanjing Jicang Nanotechnology Co. Ltd.\\\\n\\\\nFor more information about this report visit https://www.researchandmarkets.com/r/vdg3lb\\\\n\\\\nAbout ResearchAndMarkets.com\\\\r\\\\nResearchAndMarkets.com is the world's leading source for international market research reports and market data. We provide you with the latest data on international and regional markets, key industries, the top companies, new products and the latest trends.\\\\n\\\\nCONTACT: CONTACT: ResearchAndMarkets.com Laura Wood,Senior Press Manager press@researchandmarkets.com For E.S.T Office Hours Call 1-917-300-0470 For U.S./ CAN Toll Free Call 1-800-526-8630 For GMT Office Hours Call +353-1-416-8900\\\\n\\\\nView Comments\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/mxene-industry-research-report-2026-095300271.html\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [\\\"MRK.US\\\"], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"ELECTROMAGNETIC-SHIELDING\\\", \\\"ELECTRONICS\\\", \\\"ENERGY-STORAGE\\\", \\\"MARKET RESEARCH REPORTS\\\", \\\"MXENE\\\", \\\"NANOMATERIALS\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": 1, \\\"neg\\\": 0.011, \\\"neu\\\": 0.799, \\\"pos\\\": 0.19}}, {\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-03T09:50:00+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Better Buy in 2026: Bitcoin or a Broad-Market ETF? The Answer Couldn't Be Clearer for Long-Term Investors\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"Cryptocurrency prices, including Bitcoin (CRYPTO: BTC), have been pummeled during the past few months as investors have rotated out of more speculative investments to safer ones. With the threat of tariffs rearing their ugly head again and investors concerned about how artificial intelligence (AI) might disrupt established companies and industries, desire to own digital currencies is on the wane.\\\\n\\\\nThe result is that Bitcoin has tumbled, and I think there's a case for investors to put their money into a broad-market exchange-traded fund (ETF) right now. The Vanguard S&P 500 ETF(NYSEMKT: VOO) is my personal favorite. Here's why it's a better buy than Bitcoin this year.\\\\n\\\\nWill AI create the world's first trillionaire? Our team just released a report on the one little-known company, called an \\\\\\\"Indispensable Monopoly\\\\\\\" providing the critical technology Nvidia and Intel both need. Continue »Image source: Getty Images.\\\\n\\\\nRisky investments are losing their appeal\\\\n\\\\nIt wasn't all that long ago that investors had a seemingly insatiable appetite for riskier investments. Consider that Bitcoin's price reached its all-time high of more than $126,500 in October, before the recent crypto sell-off caused its price to plummet to about $69,000 as of this writing.\\\\n\\\\nThere isn't one single factor that's caused the retreat, but rather a general skepticism about some AI stocks, uncertainty about where the economy is headed amid geopolitical uncertainties, and President Donald Trump announcing new global tariffs of as much as 15% -- just after the Supreme Court struck down his previous round of tariffs.\\\\n\\\\nAdditionally, layoffs in January were the highest in that month in 17 years, and the World Economic Forum said recently that 41% of global companies are expecting to reduce their staff during the next five years because of artificial intelligence.\\\\n\\\\nBitcoin had been on a tear in a post-COVID world where tech stocks were soaring, and initial AI optimism helped lift digital currency prices. But now some investors have the sense that economic winds might be shifting, and they have pared back on Bitcoin, along with many other cryptocurrencies and other speculative investments, including quantum computing stocks.Source: YCharts.\\\\n\\\\nBoring looks beautiful right now\\\\n\\\\nWhile Bitcoin is down about 23% during the past year, the Vanguard S&P 500 ETF has been slowly and steadily climbing more than 16%.\\\\n\\\\nThe fund tracks the S&P 500, so if the market is doing well, the fund tends to perform well too. The benefit of having your money spread across the largest 500 publicly traded companies in the U.S. is that you have the potential to benefit from many areas of growth, including AI, healthcare, consumer spending, industrial production, and more.\\\\n\\\\nStory Continues\\\\n\\\\nThis strategy has, historically, been a very good one. Since the fund's inception in 2010, it has had an annual average return of 14.8%. There's no guarantee you will receive those returns in any given year, of course, but it does show that the fund's diversification can lead to impressive returns when various economic sectors are doing well.\\\\n\\\\nSome investors don't like passive ETF investing and want the ability to personally select stocks and cryptos for their portfolio. I understand the appeal, and there's nothing wrong with that strategy. But it becomes difficult when, as now, the direction of the economy and many in dustries is hazy.\\\\n\\\\nThat's why buying this Vanguard ETF makes sense right now. While other investors try to figure out which sectors and companies will benefit or be dismantled by AI, or how tariffs will affect industrial companies in the coming years, you can instead put your money into a fund that spreads out your investments into a basket of stocks.\\\\n\\\\nNot only will you be well diversified, but you also will pay a very low annual expense ratio of just 0.03%, compared to the average S&P 500 fund fee of 0.41%.That means for every $1,000 invested in the fund, you will pay just $0.30 annually.\\\\n\\\\nI don't think Bitcoin is a bad investment, but with 2026 already off to an uncertain start, loading up on the Vanguard S&P 500 ETF may look like a wise move several years from now.\\\\n\\\\nShould you buy stock in Bitcoin right now?\\\\n\\\\nBefore you buy stock in Bitcoin, consider this:\\\\n\\\\nThe Motley Fool Stock Advisor analyst team just identified what they believe are the 10 best stocks for investors to buy now… and Bitcoin wasn’t one of them. The 10 stocks that made the cut could produce monster returns in the coming years.\\\\n\\\\nConsider when Netflix made this list on December 17, 2004... if you invested $1,000 at the time of our recommendation, you’d have $519,015!* Or when Nvidia made this list on April 15, 2005... if you invested $1,000 at the time of our recommendation, you’d have $1,086,211!*\\\\n\\\\nNow, it’s worth noting Stock Advisor’s total average return is 941% — a market-crushing outperformance compared to 194% for the S&P 500. Don't miss the latest top 10 list, available with Stock Advisor, and join an investing community built by individual investors for individual investors.\\\\n\\\\nSee the 10 stocks »\\\\n\\\\n*Stock Advisor returns as of March 3, 2026.\\\\n\\\\nChris Neiger has positions in Vanguard S&P 500 ETF. The Mo\",\n    \"content_schema\": {\n      \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/schema#\",\n      \"type\": \"array\",\n      \"items\": {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"date\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"title\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"content\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"link\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"symbols\": {\n            \"type\": \"array\",\n            \"items\": {\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            }\n          },\n          \"tags\": {\n            \"type\": \"array\",\n            \"items\": {\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            }\n          },\n          \"sentiment\": {\n            \"type\": \"object\",\n            \"properties\": {\n              \"polarity\": {\n                \"type\": \"number\"\n              },\n              \"neg\": {\n                \"type\": \"number\"\n              },\n              \"neu\": {\n                \"type\": \"number\"\n              },\n              \"pos\": {\n                \"type\": \"number\"\n              }\n            },\n            \"required\": [\n              \"neg\",\n              \"neu\",\n              \"polarity\",\n              \"pos\"\n            ]\n          }\n        },\n        \"required\": [\n          \"content\",\n          \"date\",\n          \"link\",\n          \"sentiment\",\n          \"symbols\",\n          \"tags\",\n          \"title\"\n        ]\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"elapsed_time_ms\": 1737.72,\n  \"cost\": 6.5\n}","cwd":"/Users/lynch/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772532327593}}
{"type":"message","id":"dda46a69","parentId":"c3b40e8a","timestamp":"2026-03-03T10:05:42.134Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I got financial news from EODHD with sentiment data. The sentiment has a \"polarity\" score ranging from -1 to 1, not a \"heat\" score of 0-100. But this is similar.\n\nLooking at the data, I can see:\n- First article: polarity: 0.769 \n- Second article: polarity: 0.997\n- Third article: polarity: 1.0\n\nThese are all very positive. But this isn't a \"heat\" metric - it's sentiment polarity.\n\nThe user asked for \"热度≥80\" (heat ≥80). This could be:\n1. A specific metric from Finnhub that I'm not finding\n2. The user might be referring to engagement/popularity metrics\n3. Or they might be confusing sentiment with heat\n\nSince Finnhub News API is not working on QVeris, I should report this to the user. Let me also check if there are any articles with high \"heat\" in the EODHD data by looking at engagement or other metrics. The EODHD news doesn't seem to have a \"heat\" metric either.\n\nActually, wait - let me check the QVeris X hot topics tracker - that might have engagement metrics that could represent \"heat\".","thinkingSignature":"b81626f2f990e77d84209676a936657b18146a06ba7a436b615f7c4314b82bbb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mw5693vp4ree_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace && node scripts/qveris_tool.mjs execute \"qveris_social.x_domain_hot_topics_v1\" --params '{\"domains\": [\"Finance\"], \"limit\": 10, \"min_engagement\": 100}'","timeout":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":37744,"output":343,"cacheRead":13984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":52071,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772532327597}}
